# Keep "Edited on" current in Studies

Every study under `Studies/` carries an `**Edited on:**` field directly below
the `**Author:**` line. Whenever you make a substantive content change to a
study's markdown, update that field to the current date and time before you
finish.

- Format: `**Edited on:** Month D, YYYY, h:mm AM/PM IST` (e.g. `June 16, 2026, 11:16 AM IST`).
- Use the real current date/time, not a copied value from another file.
- If the field is missing, add it on its own line immediately after the `**Author:**` line, separated by a blank line.
- After editing the markdown, regenerate the matching PDF using the internal
  pipeline in `.cursor/rules/md-to-pdf.mdc` (never ad-hoc converters).

- Also update the study's `Status` column in the catalog tables of **both**
  `Studies/README.md` and `Studies/index.html`. Status values:
  - `Ongoing` — no document uploaded yet (italic title, no PDF).
  - `Draft<br>Last updated on: <date>, <time> IST` — a document/PDF exists but is
    not finalized (date/time matching the study's `**Edited on:**` field).
  - `Released<br>Last updated on: <date>, <time> IST` — only once a study is
    explicitly finalized/released.

Skip the update only for trivial, non-content edits (e.g. fixing a typo in this
rule's own example).
